      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MELFIELD SORYT (6) made an encouraging return to the Grima yard when runner-up from this barrier here last week, beaten a head. Has won both times she has attempted this shorter distance here so can atone. Leading hope. MAJOR AUSTIN (1) added to a string of top-two finishes when held up last week at Penrith. Overcame a wide barrier to cruise home here prior. The ace draw should ensure a cosy run. Big chance. PAPA JOE (5) returns to the front row and came from a similar barrier to this to win at Bathurst the last time he started from there. MODERN MISCHIEF (2) was held up fresh but draws better so look for improvement.",
